# Graduation Project - Full-Stack Web Application

## Project Overview

This is a modern full-stack web application built as a graduation project. It serves as a foundation for scalable web applications with robust authentication, internationalization, and modern development practices.

## Key Technologies

### Frontend Stack

- **Next.js 15.5.2** - React framework with App Router and typed routes
- **React 19.1.0** - Latest React with modern features
- **TypeScript 5** - Type-safe development
- **Tailwind CSS 4** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **Radix UI** - Accessible component primitives
- **shadcn/ui** - Pre-built component library
- **next-themes** - Dark/light theme support

### Backend & Database

- **Better Auth 1.3.7** - Modern authentication library
- **Drizzle ORM 0.44.5** - Type-safe database toolkit
- **PostgreSQL** - Primary database (via @neondatabase/serverless)
- **Resend** - Email service provider

### Development Tools

- **Turbopack** - Fast bundler for development
- **ESLint 9** - Code linting
- **Prettier** - Code formatting
- **Husky** - Git hooks
- **lint-staged** - Pre-commit linting

### Key Features

- ✅ Authentication system (email/password + GitHub OAuth)
- ✅ Email verification
- ✅ Internationalization (English/Vietnamese)
- ✅ Dark/light theme switching
- ✅ Type-safe forms with validation
- ✅ Responsive design
- ✅ Email templates with React Email

## Architecture Patterns

### File Organization

- **Feature-based structure** in `/src/features/`
- **Shared components** in `/src/components/`
- **Database schemas** in `/src/db/schemas/`
- **Internationalization** in `/src/locales/`
- **Type-safe constants** in `/src/constants/`

### Authentication Flow

- Uses Better Auth with Drizzle adapter
- Email verification required for new accounts
- GitHub OAuth integration
- Username + email login support
- Server-side session management

### Internationalization Strategy

- Cookie-based locale storage (not URL-based routing)
- Next-intl for translation management
- Supports English (en) and Vietnamese (vi)
- Client and server-side locale utilities

## Development Guidelines

### Always Prefer

- TypeScript over JavaScript
- Feature-based organization over type-based
- Server-side operations for sensitive data
- Zod schemas for validation
- React Hook Form for form management
- Tailwind CSS for styling

### Key Files to Reference

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [src/lib/auth.ts](mdc:src/lib/auth.ts) - Authentication configuration
- [src/constants/locale.ts](mdc:src/constants/locale.ts) - Locale configuration
